Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Roughly chop @walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and
rinse @cannellini beans{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion greens, walnuts, @olive oil{2%tsp} juice from one
lemon wedge (two wedges for 4), a pinch of lemon zest, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and
@black pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant and tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/4%cup} a pinch of salt, and
pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, mashing about half the
beans with the back of a #wooden spoon{}, until beans are creamy and have thickened,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}. Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered until ready to serve.

While beans cook, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook
until browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Let pan
cool for ~{1%minute}, then wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes
> per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add @red pepper jam{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, and
@butter{1%tablespoon}; cook, whisking, until butter has melted and sauce has
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Slice steak crosswise.

Divide beans between #shallow bowls{} and top with sliced steak. Spoon pan sauce over
steak and top with gremolata. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Slice chicken or steak against the grain.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.